# On the Distinction Between Zero and Infinity

An exploration of why zero and infinity are fundamentally distinct mathematical objects, approached through four different frameworks: real analysis, proof by contradiction, limit theory, and set-theoretic cardinality.

Written as part of independent study of Tao's Analysis I (2026).

